evacuations. The city
of Richmond has a mandatory and
voluntary

29:22.461 --> 29:24.196 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
evacuation.

29:24.229 --> 29:28.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have large parts of the
unincorporated
area of the county that have
been affected,

29:28.600 --> 29:31.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as the river crests in Richmond
is then going
to move down into the southern
part of the

29:31.670 --> 29:40.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
county. A good part of the
southern part of
the county has levees. All our
leveed areas

29:40.779 --> 29:46.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are in fine shape. All the lid
operators are
doing a great job.

29:46.051 --> 29:51.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So there's no worry there. But
then once we
get past the lid areas, we're
looking at some

29:51.790 --> 29:58.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
other areas where it is a
combination of rural
houses, and also more
bottomland, where there's

29:58.163 --> 29:59.865 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
cattle and horses.

29:59.898 --> 30:05.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A lot of those individuals have
taken heed
of the warnings and have moved a
lot of the

30:05.337 --> 30:07.105 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people and livestock out of the
way.

30:07.139 --> 30:11.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
Jeff Braun, the
emergency management coordinator
in Fort Bend

30:11.410 --> 30:14.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
County, thanks so much for
joining us. I know
it's a busy day for you. Thank
you.

30:14.312 --> 30:16.415 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFF BRAUN: Thank you.

30:16.448 --> 30:20.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: From where the
water is
to where it may be going.
Houston, which has

30:20.385 --> 30:23.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
