waters in recent
years, is bracing for
floodwaters to come

30:23.455 --> 30:25.290 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
its way.

30:25.323 --> 30:28.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Michael Walter is with the
Office of Emergency
Management for the city. He
joins me now.

30:28.627 --> 30:33.465 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, lot of times, the
floodwaters in Texas,
they basically go through
Houston to get to

30:33.498 --> 30:35.701 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
