moved into this
world of torture.

49:22.960 --> 49:27.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Torture, for me, were things
like stress positions,
and in particular sleep
deprivation. And I

49:27.598 --> 49:32.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
know that a good number of
Americans would
scoff and even laugh and suggest
that we can

49:32.269 --> 49:37.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
go as far as water-boarding. And
I think you
can see just how lost we are in
this idea

49:37.641 --> 49:41.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that there are different levels
of abuse and
different levels of
interrogation.

49:41.912 --> 49:46.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's anything that violates
another human
being's will is torture. And, as
Americans,

49:46.884 --> 49:50.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that's the attitude we
